For example:
	â€¢	For interest-rate swaps â†’ compare your DV01 (dollar value of a basis point) exposure vs the average DV01 traded per day in that tenor.
	â€¢	For options â†’ compare your vega (or vanna/volga) vs the average daily vega turnover in that maturity/bucket.

When the ratio is large (say, >5Ã— daily turnover), the trade is â€œhard to replaceâ€: if you tried to unwind it, the market impact per bp or per vol point would be material.

